other_tests.findings: Sinus rhythm at baseline with preexcitation in a pattern of a midseptal accessory pathway. During recovery, sinus node rhythm at 114 bpm with prolonged PR interval and right bundle-branch block morphology without preexcitation.
Ventricular preexcitation at baseline with no inducible arrhythmias. Preserved HV interval during pacing; indicates potentially a fasiculoventricular AP.
other_tests.changes_over_time: No change in the degree of preexcitation despite decremental AV node conduction.

other_tests.findings: Increased threshold of RV lead from 0.75 V to 2.0 V.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Indicated symptoms of presyncope which led to reprogramming of the pacemaker output to 4.0 V.

other_tests.findings: Significant variability of myofiber size with disturbed intermyofibrillar network; presence of internal nuclei and eosinophilic material; no active inflammatory changes.
Evidence of restrictive lung disease with diaphragm dysfunction.
